A chieftain of the All Progressives Congress, APC, from Abia State and immediate past Pro-Chancellor and Chairman, Governing Council of the Federal University of Calabar (UNICAL), Senator Nkechi Nwaogu, has applauded the National Working Committee of the party for standing for justice and equity in ensuring that power is successfully returned to southern Nigeria. She also lauded the determination and doggedness of the APC northern Governors who stood firm for the actualisation of a presidential candidate of southern Nigeria extraction. Nwaogu, who was also Abia Central Senatorial aspirant in the just concluded primary election, stated this in a statement issued to journalists in Umuahia, the state capital, also called on all the aspirants that contested to come together and build a progressive party that will be capacitated to defeat any opposition party in 2023. “We should take cognizance that the primary election victory of the national leader of our party is not for him alone but for the collective interest of our party members and Nigerians in general,” she said. Senator Nwaogu urged the former Lagos State Governor, Asiwaju Bola Ahmed Tinubu to bring everybody on board irrespective of their belief and ideology to work harmoniously for a successful general election in 2023. She congratulated Tinubu, on his victory in the recently concluded presidential primaries of the APC.